    options: ['Nathu La (4,310 m) — reopened for trade in 2006 after being closed since 1962 war', 'Zoji La (3,528 m) — connects Srinagar with Kargil and Ladakh across J&K', 'Bum La (4,658 m) — connects Tawang in Arunachal Pradesh with Tibet', 'Lipu Lekh (5,334 m) — connects Uttarakhand with Tibet, used for Kailash Mansarovar Yatra'],
    shortcut: 'Nathu La = 4,310 m | Sikkim → Tibet | Reopened 2006 | Zoji La = 3,528 m | Kashmir → Ladakh | Only route Kashmir-Ladakh in winter | Banihal Pass = Jawahar Tunnel',
    detail: 'Nathu La (4,310 m) in Sikkim connects India with Tibet. One of three open India-China trading posts. Reopened 2006. Zoji La (3,528 m) connects Srinagar with Kargil/Ladakh — strategically vital, only land route between Kashmir and Ladakh in winter. Banihal Pass has the Jawahar Tunnel underneath it, connecting Jammu with Kashmir.',
    context: 'SSC CGL Recurring', examProb: 'Hot',
    tamilNote: 'நாது லா = 4,310 மீ | சிக்கிம் → திபெத் | 2006-ல் வர்த்தகத்திற்காக மீண்டும் திறக்கப்பட்டது. ஜோஜி லா = காஷ்மீர் → லடாக் இணைப்பு.',
  },
  {
    id: 16, category: 'Mountains & Passes', topic: 'Palghat Gap',
    question: 'Which is the most significant gap in the Western Ghats?',
    answer: 'Palghat Gap (Palakkad Gap) — 30 km wide, 300 m elevation, between Nilgiri Hills and Anaimalai Hills in Kerala',
    options: ['Palghat Gap (Palakkad Gap) — 30 km wide, 300 m elevation, between Nilgiri Hills and Anaimalai Hills in Kerala', 'Bhor Ghat — mountain pass in Western Ghats connecting Mumbai with Pune via Deccan', 'Thal Ghat — mountain pass in Western Ghats connecting Mumbai with Nashik via Deccan', 'Shenkottai Gap — southernmost gap in the Western Ghats between Kerala and Tamil Nadu'],
    shortcut: 'Palghat Gap = 30 km wide | 300 m elevation | Between Nilgiris & Anaimalais | Kerala ↔ Tamil Nadu | Influences monsoon | SW monsoon enters TN here',
    detail: 'Palghat Gap is a low mountain pass in the Western Ghats between Nilgiri Hills and Anaimalai Hills. About 30 km wide and 300 m elevation. Provides easy connectivity between Kerala and Tamil Nadu. It influences regional climate by allowing the SW monsoon to enter Tamil Nadu. Other gaps: Bhor Ghat (Mumbai-Pune), Thal Ghat (Mumbai-Nashik).',
    context: 'SSC CGL 2023', examProb: 'Confirmed',
    tamilNote: 'பாலக்காடு கணவாய் = 30 கி.மீ அகலம் | நீலகிரி & ஆனைமலை மலைகளுக்கு இடையே | கேரளா ↔ தமிழ்நாடு இணைப்பு | தென்மேற்குப் பருவமழை தமிழ்நாட்டிற்கு இங்கு நுழைகிறது.',
  },
  {
    id: 17, category: 'Mountains & Passes', topic: 'Aravalli Range',
    question: 'Which is the oldest fold mountain range in India?',
    answer: 'Aravalli Range — stretches 800 km from Delhi to Gujarat, highest peak is Guru Shikhar (1,722 m)',
    options: ['Aravalli Range — stretches 800 km from Delhi to Gujarat, highest peak is Guru Shikhar (1,722 m)', 'Vindhya Range — stretches across central India, separating Indo-Gangetic plains from Deccan Plateau', 'Satpura Range — stretches 900 km through MP and Maharashtra, highest peak is Dhupgarh (1,350 m)', 'Eastern Ghats — discontinuous range along east coast, broken by rivers Godavari, Krishna, Cauvery'],
    shortcut: 'Aravalli = oldest fold mountain in India | 800 km | Delhi → Gujarat | Guru Shikhar = 1,722 m (Mount Abu) | Divides Rajasthan: Thar Desert (west) & plains (east)',
    detail: 'The Aravalli Range is one of the oldest fold mountains in the world, running approximately 800 km from Delhi to Gujarat through Rajasthan. It acts as a water divide between the Indus and Ganga systems. It blocks the Arabian Sea monsoon from reaching northwest Rajasthan, creating the Thar Desert on the western side.',
    context: 'SSC CGL 2021', examProb: 'High',
    tamilNote: 'அரவல்லி = இந்தியாவின் மிகப் பழமையான மடிப்பு மலைத்தொடர். 800 கி.மீ | டெல்லியிலிருந்து குஜராத் வரை. குரு சிகர் = 1,722 மீ.',
  },

