    id: 25, category: 'National Parks & Wildlife', topic: 'Jim Corbett National Park',
    question: 'Which is India\'s first national park and when was it established?',
    answer: 'Jim Corbett NP (Uttarakhand) — established 1936 as Hailey NP, first Tiger Reserve under Project Tiger (1973)',
    options: ['Jim Corbett NP (Uttarakhand) — established 1936 as Hailey NP, first Tiger Reserve under Project Tiger (1973)', 'Kaziranga NP (Assam) — established 1974 as a UNESCO World Heritage Site for one-horned rhinoceros', 'Gir Forest NP (Gujarat) — established 1965 as the sole habitat of wild Asiatic Lions', 'Kanha NP (Madhya Pradesh) — established 1955, inspiration for Kipling\'s The Jungle Book'],
    shortcut: 'Corbett = 1936 | Oldest NP | Originally Hailey NP | Uttarakhand | 1st Tiger Reserve (1973 Project Tiger) | On Ramganga River',
    detail: 'Jim Corbett NP was established in 1936 as Hailey National Park, making it India\'s oldest. Located in Uttarakhand on the Ramganga River. It became the first Tiger Reserve in 1973 under Project Tiger (launched by Indira Gandhi). Named after hunter-turned-conservationist Jim Corbett. Total area: 520.8 sq km.',
    context: 'SSC CGL 2021-2024', examProb: 'Hot',
    tamilNote: 'ஜிம் கார்பெட் = இந்தியாவின் முதல் தேசியப் பூங்கா (1936). உத்தரகண்ட். புலிக் காப்பகம் (1973 புராஜெக்ட் டைகர்).',
  },
