    detail: 'Sundarbans NP in West Bengal is part of the largest mangrove forest in the world, situated in the Ganga-Brahmaputra delta. Named after the dominant Sundari trees (Heritiera fomes). It is a UNESCO World Heritage Site, Tiger Reserve, and Biosphere Reserve. The mangroves extend into Bangladesh.',
