  {
    id: 29, category: 'National Parks & Wildlife', topic: 'Keibul Lamjao NP',
    question: 'Which is the only floating national park in the world?',
    answer: 'Keibul Lamjao NP (Manipur) — located on Loktak Lake, home to the endangered Sangai deer (Brow-antlered deer)',
    options: ['Keibul Lamjao NP (Manipur) — located on Loktak Lake, home to the endangered Sangai deer (Brow-antlered deer)', 'Dibru-Saikhowa NP (Assam) — located on Brahmaputra floodplain, home to feral horses and tigers', 'Nameri NP (Assam) — located on the Jia-Bhoroli River, home to elephants and tigers', 'Namdapha NP (Arunachal Pradesh) — located in eastern Himalayas, home to snow leopards and tigers'],
    shortcut: 'Keibul Lamjao = Manipur | Only floating NP | Loktak Lake = largest freshwater lake in NE | Sangai deer (endangered) | "Phumdis" = floating vegetation mats',
    detail: 'Keibul Lamjao NP in Manipur is the world\'s only floating national park, located on Loktak Lake (largest freshwater lake in NE India). The park floats on "Phumdis" — heterogeneous masses of vegetation, soil, and organic matter. It is the last natural habitat of the endangered Sangai (Eld\'s deer / Brow-antlered deer), the state animal of Manipur.',
    context: 'SSC CGL 2022', examProb: 'Confirmed',
    tamilNote: 'கெய்புல் லம்ஜாவ் = மணிப்பூர் | உலகின் ஒரே மிதக்கும் தேசியப் பூங்கா | லோக்டாக் ஏரி | சங்கை மான் (ஆபத்தில் உள்ள இனம்).',
  },
