    answer: 'Rabi (Oct-Mar): Wheat, Barley, Mustard, Gram | Kharif (Jun-Sep): Rice, Maize, Cotton, Jowar, Bajra, Sugarcane',
    options: ['Rabi (Oct-Mar): Wheat, Barley, Mustard, Gram | Kharif (Jun-Sep): Rice, Maize, Cotton, Jowar, Bajra, Sugarcane', 'Rabi (Jun-Sep): Rice, Cotton, Sugarcane | Kharif (Oct-Mar): Wheat, Mustard, Gram, Barley', 'Rabi (Jun-Sep): Wheat, Mustard, Gram | Kharif (Nov-Apr): Rice, Cotton, Jowar, Bajra', 'Rabi (Mar-Jun): Watermelon, Cucumber, Muskmelon | Kharif (Oct-Mar): Wheat, Gram, Mustard'],
    shortcut: 'Rabi = Winter (Oct sow → Mar harvest) = Wheat, Barley, Gram, Mustard | Kharif = Monsoon (Jun sow → Sep harvest) = Rice, Maize, Cotton, Jowar | Zaid = Summer = Watermelon, Cucumber',
    detail: 'Rabi crops are winter crops sown in October and harvested in March: wheat, barley, gram (chickpea), mustard, peas. Kharif crops are monsoon crops sown in June and harvested in September-October: rice, maize, cotton, jowar, bajra, sugarcane, groundnut. Zaid crops are summer crops: watermelon, cucumber, muskmelon. India is the 2nd largest food grain producer after China.',
