    detail: 'Similipal NP in Odisha was officially designated as India\'s 107th national park in April 2025. It is a Tiger Reserve and Biosphere Reserve, famous for melanistic (black) tigers. With this, India has 107 national parks covering ~44,403 sq km (1.35% of land area). Madhya Pradesh has the most national parks (9), tied with Andaman & Nicobar Islands.',
