    tamilNote: 'சிமிலிபால் = இந்தியாவின் 107வது தேசியப் பூங்கா | ஒடிசா | ஏப்ரல் 2025. கருப்பு புலிகள் (melanistic) காணப்படும் இடம்.',
  },
  {
    id: 74, category: 'Current Affairs (Geo)', topic: 'New Ramsar Sites in India',
    question: 'How many Ramsar Wetland sites does India have (as of 2025)?',
    answer: '82 Ramsar sites (as of 2025) — India has the most Ramsar sites in South Asia',
    options: ['82 Ramsar sites (as of 2025) — India has the most Ramsar sites in South Asia', '54 Ramsar sites (as of 2025) — India has the 3rd most Ramsar sites in Asia after China and Japan', '64 Ramsar sites (as of 2025) — India has the 2nd most Ramsar sites in South Asia after Sri Lanka', '49 Ramsar sites (as of 2025) — India has the most Ramsar sites in the Indian subcontinent'],
    shortcut: 'Ramsar = 82 sites (2025) | UP leads with most sites | Largest: Sundarbans (WB) | Smallest: Renuka (HP) | Chilika Lake (Odisha) = largest coastal lagoon | Ramsar Convention = 1971, Iran',
    detail: 'India has 82 Ramsar sites (as of 2025), the highest in South Asia. UP has the most Ramsar sites. Largest: Sundarbans (West Bengal). Smallest: Renuka (Himachal Pradesh). Chilika Lake (Odisha) is the largest coastal lagoon in India and a Ramsar site. The Ramsar Convention (1971, Ramsar, Iran) is an international treaty for wetland conservation.',
