  {
    id: 77, category: 'Soil & Climate', topic: 'Desert Soil',
    question: 'What are the characteristics of desert (arid) soil in India?',
    answer: 'Sandy, low moisture, low organic content, high salinity — found in western Rajasthan, parts of Gujarat and Haryana',
    options: ['Sandy, low moisture, low organic content, high salinity — found in western Rajasthan, parts of Gujarat and Haryana', 'Clayey, high moisture retention, self-ploughing, cracks when dry — found in Maharashtra and Gujarat Deccan', 'Humus-rich, acidic, dark brown color, supports plantation crops — found in Himalayan foothills and Western Ghats', 'Porous, red due to iron oxide, low fertility — found in crystalline rock regions of eastern and southern India'],
    shortcut: 'Desert soil = Sandy + Saline | Low moisture + low humus | W. Rajasthan, Gujarat, Haryana | Can be productive with irrigation (Indira Gandhi Canal) | Contains kankar (calcium carbonate)',
    detail: 'Desert (arid) soil is found in western Rajasthan, parts of Gujarat and Haryana. Sandy texture, low moisture retention, low organic matter, high salinity. Contains kankar (calcium carbonate nodules). Can be made productive with irrigation — the Indira Gandhi Canal (Rajasthan Canal) has transformed parts of Thar Desert into agricultural land.',
    context: 'SSC CGL 2024', examProb: 'High',
    tamilNote: 'பாலைவன மண் = மணல், குறைந்த ஈரப்பதம், உப்புத்தன்மை. மேற்கு ராஜஸ்தான். இந்திரா காந்தி கால்வாய் மூலம் பயிரிடலாம்.',
  },
  {
