    detail: 'The Ring of Fire (Pacific Ring of Fire) is a horseshoe-shaped zone around the Pacific Ocean, approximately 40,000 km long. It has 75% of the world\'s active volcanoes and about 90% of world earthquakes. Countries on the Ring: Japan, Philippines, Indonesia, New Zealand, Chile, Alaska (USA), Canada. It results from tectonic plate boundaries.',
