    detail: 'Bering Strait separates Asia (Russia/Siberia) from North America (Alaska, USA). About 85 km wide. Named after Danish explorer Vitus Bering (1728). The International Date Line passes nearby. During the Ice Age, a land bridge (Beringia) existed here, allowing human migration from Asia to Americas.',
