    detail: 'Sabarmati River (371 km) originates from the Aravalli Range in Rajasthan and flows through Ahmedabad, Gujarat into the Gulf of Khambat. Mahatma Gandhi established his famous Sabarmati Ashram on its banks in 1917. The Sabarmati Riverfront Development Project in Ahmedabad is a major urban renewal initiative.',
