  },
  {
    id: 87, category: 'Dams & Irrigation', topic: 'Chambal River Dams',
    question: 'Name the three major dams on the Chambal River.',
    answer: 'Gandhi Sagar Dam (MP) → Rana Pratap Sagar Dam (Rajasthan) → Jawahar Sagar Dam (Rajasthan)',
    options: ['Gandhi Sagar Dam (MP) → Rana Pratap Sagar Dam (Rajasthan) → Jawahar Sagar Dam (Rajasthan)', 'Matatila Dam (UP) → Rajghat Dam (UP/MP) → Paricha Dam (UP) — on Betwa River', 'Pong Dam (HP) → Ranjit Sagar Dam (HP/J&K) → Shahpur Kandi Dam (Punjab) — on Ravi-Beas system', 'Tilaiya Dam (Jharkhand) → Maithon Dam (Jharkhand/WB) → Panchet Dam (Jharkhand) — on Damodar River'],
    shortcut: 'Chambal = tributary of Yamuna | 3 dams: Gandhi Sagar (MP) → Rana Pratap Sagar (Raj) → Jawahar Sagar (Raj) | Chambal famous for ravines/badlands | National Chambal Sanctuary',
    detail: 'Chambal River is a major tributary of the Yamuna. Three dams in cascade: Gandhi Sagar (MP), Rana Pratap Sagar (Rajasthan), and Jawahar Sagar (Rajasthan). The Chambal region is famous for its ravines/badlands. National Chambal Sanctuary is known for the critically endangered Gharial crocodile and Gangetic dolphin.',
    context: 'SSC CGL 2023', examProb: 'High',
    tamilNote: 'சம்பல் நதி = யமுனையின் துணைநதி. 3 அணைகள்: காந்தி சாகர் (ம.பி.) → ராணா பிரதாப் சாகர் → ஜவஹர் சாகர் (ராஜஸ்தான்).',
  },
  {
    id: 88, category: 'World Geography', topic: 'Ocean Currents',
    question: 'Name an important warm ocean current and a cold ocean current.',
    answer: 'Warm: Gulf Stream (Atlantic, N. America → Europe) | Cold: Humboldt/Peru Current (Pacific, S. America west coast)',
    options: ['Warm: Gulf Stream (Atlantic, N. America → Europe) | Cold: Humboldt/Peru Current (Pacific, S. America west coast)', 'Warm: Labrador Current (N. Atlantic, Canada) | Cold: Agulhas Current (Indian Ocean, South Africa)', 'Warm: California Current (N. Pacific, USA) | Cold: North Atlantic Drift (N. Atlantic, Europe)', 'Warm: Benguela Current (S. Atlantic, Africa) | Cold: Kuroshio Current (N. Pacific, Japan)'],
    shortcut: 'Warm: Gulf Stream (N. Atlantic), Kuroshio (N. Pacific) | Cold: Humboldt/Peru (S. Pacific), Labrador (N. Atlantic) | Warm + Cold meeting = rich fishing | Gulf Stream warms Europe',
    detail: 'Warm currents: Gulf Stream (North Atlantic, warms Western Europe), Kuroshio (North Pacific), Agulhas (Indian Ocean). Cold currents: Humboldt/Peru (Pacific, South America), Labrador (North Atlantic), Benguela (South Atlantic). Where warm and cold currents meet, they create rich fishing grounds (e.g., Grand Banks of Newfoundland). Coriolis effect deflects currents.',
    context: 'SSC CGL 2024', examProb: 'High',
    tamilNote: 'வெப்ப நீரோட்டம்: கல்ஃப் ஸ்ட்ரீம் (ஐரோப்பாவை சூடாக்கும்). குளிர் நீரோட்டம்: ஹம்போல்ட் (தென் அமெரிக்கா). இவை சந்திக்கும் இடம் = மீன் பிடி தளம்.',
