    detail: 'Houthi rebel attacks on commercial shipping in the Red Sea and Bab-el-Mandeb Strait (starting late 2023, intensifying in 2024) disrupted one of the world\'s busiest shipping routes. Ships were forced to reroute around the Cape of Good Hope (Africa), adding 10-15 days and significant costs. Suez Canal traffic dropped sharply. This affected global trade, including India\'s oil imports.',
