    detail: 'Damodar Valley Corporation (DVC) was established in 1948 as India\'s first multipurpose river valley project, modeled on the Tennessee Valley Authority (TVA) of the USA. It manages the Damodar River system across Jharkhand and West Bengal. Tilaiya Dam was the first dam built by DVC. The Damodar was once called the "Sorrow of Bengal" due to frequent floods.',
