    detail: 'The Mumbai Trans Harbour Link (MTHL), named Atal Bihari Vajpayee Sewri-Nhava Sheva Atal Setu, is India\'s longest sea bridge at 21.8 km. Opened on 12 January 2024. It connects Sewri (Mumbai) with Nhava Sheva (Navi Mumbai). 6-lane bridge that reduces travel time from 90 minutes to about 20 minutes. Cost: approximately Rs 18,000 crore.',
