    shortcut: 'Gulf of Kutch Marine NP = Gujarat | 1st marine NP (1982) | Gulf of Mannar = TN | Coral reefs, dugongs | Mahatma Gandhi Marine NP = Wandoor, Andaman | Coral reefs + sea turtles',
    detail: 'Gulf of Kutch Marine NP (Gujarat) was India\'s first marine national park (1982). Protects coral reefs, mangroves, and marine biodiversity. Gulf of Mannar Marine NP (TN) protects coral reefs, dugongs, and sea turtles. Mahatma Gandhi Marine NP (Wandoor, Andaman) has pristine coral reefs. India has 4 major coral reef areas: Gulf of Kutch, Gulf of Mannar, Andaman & Nicobar, Lakshadweep.',
    context: 'SSC CGL 2024', examProb: 'High',
    tamilNote: 'கச்சின் வளைகுடா கடல் NP = குஜராத் (1982, முதல் கடல் NP). மன்னார் வளைகுடா = தமிழ்நாடு. மகாத்மா காந்தி = அந்தமான்.',
